All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Account
    The Account class contains the properties and methods associated with the Account object.
    AccountDatabase
    The AccountDatabase class is the container class that represents an account database as an array of items.
    Checking
    Checking is a subclass of Account with the properties and methods associated with the Checking object Properties and methods inherited from Account class Additional methods include monthlyInterest, monthlyFee, toString, and equals
    CheckingTest
    The CheckingTest class is a class that runs JUnit Tests on the monthlyInterest/Fee methods of Checking Each test case uses the assertEquals method to compare expected and actual interest/fees
    Date
    The Date class contains the properties and methods associated with the Date object.
    DateTest
    The DateTest class is the JUnit test class, where the method isValid is tested with individual test cases Each test case uses the assertFalse or assertTrue methods to validate dates
    MoneyMarket
    MoneyMarket is a subclass of Account with the properties and methods associated with the MoneyMarket object Properties and methods inherited from Account class Additional methods include monthlyInterest, monthlyFee, toString, equals
    MoneyMarketTest
    The MoneyMarketTest class is a class that runs JUnit Tests on the monthlyInterest/Fee methods of MoneyMarket Each test case uses the assertEquals method to compare expected and actual interest/fees
    Profile
    The Profile class contains the properties and methods associated with the Profile object.
    RunProject2
    The RunProject2 class is the driver class to run Project 2.
    Savings
    Savings is a subclass of Account with the properties and methods associated with the Savings object Properties and methods inherited from Account class Additional methods include monthlyInterest, monthlyFee, toString, and equals
    TransactionManager
    The TransactionManager class is the user interface class that handles inputs commands, outputs data, and messages.
